  "title": "Senior/Assembly Technician (Electronics Industry)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Operate and maintain manufacturing facilities, equipment, jigs and fixtures, such as assembly jig and machinery, calibration equipment and Tester, Glue Dispenser, Ultrasonic cleaner, conveyors, and automated machinery, to ensure optimal      productivity and efficiency.</li><li>Monitor production processes, identify any issues or deviations from specifications, and take corrective action as necessary.</li><li>Conduct regular equipment calibration and correlation checks throughout the production process to ensure consistency of product specifications and quality\nstandards and maintain stable production yield.</li><li> Perform routine preventative maintenance on production equipment to ensure optimal performance and minimize downtime</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong mechanical and electrical aptitude and technical skills to operate and troubleshoot manufacturing equipment.</li><li>Knowledge of manufacturing processes, equipment, and quality control procedures and techniques.</li><li>Knowledge safety protocols and procedures in a manufacturing setting. </li></ul><p>Interested Candidates, Please send your Detailed Resume stating Past Employments, Including Reasons of Leaving, Current / Last Drawn and Expected Salary to quenni.chen@manfield.com.sg / Watsapp 86887476</p><p>EA License No: 95C2823</p><p>EA Personnel No: R1222837</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Quennie  Chen</p>",
